Italfari is a vegan restaurant located at 313 Utica Avenue in the Crown Heights section of Brooklyn, NY between President and Union streets. Here you can get freshly made juices, vegan meals and vegan patties. There is limited seating available. It is not far from the Utica Avenue subway station (3 and 4 trains) at Eastern Parkway. Accessible by the B46 bus.

They will have customers waiting to order food (happened several times), and there is no one to serve. Great food; reasonably priced. Friendly staff. If you are vegetarian, vegan, or just conscientious about what you eat, this is a good spot to buy your food from. It is a small take out restaurant, but it was worthwhile that I made the stop there.

I stop here at ItalFari for delicious, tasty, well seasoned foods, and scrumptious juices or smoothies, as often as I am able.  The music is always blasting, and the vibe is laid back; reminiscent of home Trinidad.  They juice what is on the menu, or I would tweak a menu item to my taste, get a recommendation from the friendly staff, or try something that just looks appealing. I highly recommend this place, and would make a special trip just to enjoy their fare.  This is a great place to get some food, a healthy beverage, and go chill at  the park up the street on a nice summer day.  Also, ItalFari is an ideal place to buy a fresh, healthy, juiced drink to sip on as I explore the shops along Utica.  An excellent vegetarian establishment that has been there for years, and I have enjoyed for as many years.
